OL,3,CWriter of Mr Bates v The Post Office
OL,4,Csays more people are asking her for
OL,5,Chelp
OL,7,FWhen I ask Ms Hughes what she plans to
OL,8,Fdo next, she responds: "I'm tired. The
OL,9,Fpast month has been a whirlwind, and I
OL,10,Fneed to take some time and regroup."
OL,12,FThis is understandable.
OL,14,FIt is not often the writers of TV
OL,15,Fdramas find themselves so in-demand.
OL,16,FThat is normally the territory of the
OL,17,Factors who deliver the lines on screen.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/9
