OL,3,CWriter of Mr Bates v The Post Office
OL,4,Csays more people are asking her for
OL,5,Chelp
OL,7,FWhat followed was three years of
OL,8,Fintense research as she travelled
OL,9,Faround the country to talk to the
OL,10,Fvictims of what has been called one of
OL,11,Fthe biggest miscarriages of justice in
OL,12,FUK history.
OL,14,FHer task was to whittle everything
OL,15,Fdown, to focus on a handful of the
OL,16,Fvictims, which was understandably
OL,17,Fdifficult.
OL,19,FShe was left staggered and in
OL,20,Fdisbelief at what they told her.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/9
